  <name>Vigil</name>
  <summary>Accountability screenshot software</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Vigil takes screenshots of your screen at random intervals and uploads
      them to a server where an accountability partner can review them. This
      helps people who want external accountability for their screen usage.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Random-interval screenshots that cannot be predicted</li>
      <li>Works on both X11 and Wayland (including Elementary OS 7 and 8)</li>
      <li>Uploads to a configurable HTTPS endpoint</li>
      <li>Queues screenshots for upload when offline</li>
      <li>Detects and reports when monitoring is disabled</li>
      <li>Follows elementary OS Human Interface Guidelines</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

